cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the interpretation of deep neural networks in terms of information theory and feature extraction, which are core topics in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the application of deep neural networks in computer vision tasks, which suggests the possibility of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a relevant category. Finally, the paper provides insights into the internal computation results of deep neural networks, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
